page.title: 01Our 4km x 3km Block
page.content: Our block contains arable farmland, most of{Immingham Docks}and the town of{Immingham. The sheltered estuary of the Humber provided an excellent site for the Docks and the town of{Immingham}grew from their existence. The dramatic rise in the population of {Immingham}is shown below: 1951.......2803 1961.......4208 1971......10205 1981......11480 Present....11580 There are 1418 Council houses and 2002 private houses. The industrial sites in the area are mostly confined to the Docks and its environs and there are very good road connections from all directions. {(Researched by Ian Huntley and Ewan {Pickwell) }
